meaningMnemonic: A <radical>middle</radical> of the road <radical>leader</radical> is likely to have an average <kanji>relationship</kanji> with everyone. He doesn’t really take sides in matters, and just stays in the middle. This makes him seem like sort of a wishy washy people pleaser, and as such his relationships with people are rarely anything more than average.
readingMnemonic: This kanji is pronounced exactly like the kanji 中 (なか). It's one of those kanji where you can figure out the reading from one of the radicals.
